OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775049067
OL,3,CWho are the four astronauts leading
OL,4,Cthe historic Artemis II mission to the
OL,5,Cmoon?
OL,7,FFour people will soon step aboard a
OL,8,Fspacecraft for the first human moon
OL,9,Fmission in more than half a century.
OL,11,FThe crew of the NASA-led Artemis II is
OL,12,Fset to depart on its 10-day mission on
OL,13,FWednesday, at around 11.24 pm BST.
OL,15,FThey represent a tapestry of historic
OL,16,Fmilestones - the first woman, the
OL,17,Ffirst person of colour, and the first
OL,18,FCanadian to be chosen for a lunar
OL,19,Fmission.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775049067
OL,3,CWho are the four astronauts leading
OL,4,Cthe historic Artemis II mission to the
OL,5,Cmoon?
OL,7,FHowever, the upcoming test flight will
OL,8,Fnot see boots on the moon just yet.
OL,9,FThe roughly 600,000-mile (965,600-
OL,10,Fkilometer) trip will see the team
OL,11,Fhurtle beyond the moon, then swing
OL,12,Fround to come straight back.
OL,14,FOn their trip, the team will be
OL,15,Fexposed to dangerous levels of
OL,16,Fradiation and is expected to lose
OL,17,Fcontact with mission control at
OL,18,Fvarious points.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
